			<div class="content" id="post-content-2837868">
									

<p>Hi-</p>
<p>Don't know if the author will see this, but &quot;imam&quot; in the Shi'ite sense is very different to &quot;imam&quot; in the Sunni sense. &quot;Imam&quot; refers to those members of Muhammad's line who Shi'ites believe are the rightful heads of the Islamic community- not to a religious dignitary. I know it's a small thing, but using it to mean a religious official or a cleric, as is done here, is rather immersion breaking. &quot;Mullah&quot; or even &quot;Ayatollah&quot; would perhaps be better.</p>

							</div>

								
					
