			<div class="content" id="post-content-3613521">
									

<p>Greetings.</p>
<p>Thank you for bringing us this excellent article, and it definitely deserves a +1! I have translated it to SCP Foundation Chinese branch, see <a href="http://scp-wiki-cn.wikidot.com/oria-001">here</a> for the translated version.</p>
<p>There is something I didn't quite get in your document. The Arabic in the last page,</p>
<blockquote>
<p>الله الأب (THE IMMUTABLE, THE INFINITE, THE EVERLASTING)</p>
</blockquote>
<p>It means God the Father, or Allāh al-ab, which is used by Arabic-speaking Christians. (You may refer to Wikipedia, article &quot;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allah">Allah</a>&quot;, section Christianity) I assume the Jibril is a Muslim, so it is not likely that he would use the term &quot;God the Father&quot;.. Is it a mistake, or there are deep meanings?</p>
<p>Perhaps it would be better using only &quot;الله&quot; ? Or you may refer to <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Names_of_God_in_Islam">Allah's other names</a> if you want to change the word..</p>

							</div>

								
